        "action": "Referendum on whether clocks should go permanently forward or backwards in UK.",
        "additional_details": "Details here:\r\n\r\nhttps://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47704345\r\n\r\nBed In Summer \r\n\r\nby Robert Louis Stevenson\r\n\r\nIn winter I get up at night\r\nAnd dress by yellow candle-light.\r\nIn summer, quite the other way,\r\nI have to go to bed by day.\r\n\r\nI have to go to bed and see\r\nThe birds still hopping on the tree,\r\nOr hear the grown-up people\u2019s feet\r\nStill going past me in the street.\r\n\r\nAnd does it not seem hard to you,\r\nWhen all the sky is clear and blue\r\nAnd I should like so much to play,\r\nTo have to go to bed by day?",
        "background": "Put it to the people - do we wish to be a nation basking in permanent, long-evenings of summer time or enjoying a lie-in during the darker mornings of winter? Larks or owls?\r\n\r\nA Referendum to lift the nation\u2019s spirit and provide a happy distraction during politically dark days.",
